        <div class="space-y-6 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <p>
                I often look for new content to consume and find it very handy when people share their readings. 
            </p>
            <p>
                So here it is, a list of books and podcasts that I read/listened to. I added personal notes for some. 
            </p>

            <table class="w-full text-sm border-collapse">
                <thead>
                    <tr class="border-b border-gray-200">
                        <th class="text-left py-2 pr-4 font-semibold text-gray-900 w-2/5">Book</th>
                        <th class="text-left py-2 font-semibold text-gray-900 w-3/5">Notes</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr class="border-b border-gray-100">
                        <td class="py-2 pr-4 align-top font-medium text-gray-900">Striking Thoughts - Bruce Lee's Wisdom for Daily Living</td>
                        <td class="py-2 align-top text-gray-600">Insightful content. Wise words that makes you think and look inside yourself. I'd have found it even better with more real-life examples and a better narrative.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr class="border-b border-gray-100">
                        <td class="py-2 pr-4 align-top font-medium text-gray-900">Autobiography of a Yogi</td>
                        <td class="py-2 align-top text-gray-600">Well told story of a well known figure in the recent spiritual world. Not so much an ancient wisdom book, more following the story of a man who lived a lot of spectacular things.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr class="border-b border-gray-100">
                        <td class="py-2 pr-4 align-top font-medium text-gray-900">Boundless: Upgrade Your Brain, Optimize Your Body & Defy Aging</td>
                        <td class="py-2 align-top text-gray-600">Information-dense book. Blueprint on everything that Ben (author) learned when testing things as a guineapig. If you're into health and brain performance like me, it's definitely worth reading.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr class="border-b border-gray-100">
                        <td class="py-2 pr-4 align-top font-medium text-gray-900">Peak</td>
                        <td class="py-2 align-top text-gray-600">Insightful book on how your brain works. Provides practical examples on how people became experts in their fields and what you can put in place to become one too.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr class="border-b border-gray-100">
                        <td class="py-2 pr-4 align-top font-medium text-gray-900">The Way to Love: The Last Meditations of Anthony de Mello</td>
                        <td class="py-2 align-top text-gray-600">Another timeless wisdom book from Anthony De Mello. Less impact on me than his other book Awareness. Nevertheless, it's also a great book that makes you grow and rethink your core beliefs.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr class="border-b border-gray-100">
                        <td class="py-2 pr-4 align-top font-medium text-gray-900">Radical Acceptance: Awakening the Love That Heals Fear and Shame</td>
                        <td class="py-2 align-top text-gray-600">The book explores buddhist concepts of loving-kindness and awareness to cope with negative feelings. There are useful, practical and actionable examples to illustrate each concept. Definitely worth reading if you sometimes experience anxiety or self-doubt.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr class="border-b border-gray-100">
                        <td class="py-2 pr-4 align-top font-medium text-gray-900">How Democracies Die</td>
                        <td class="py-2 align-top text-gray-600">Interesting book on how leaders influence nations and the world. Good part on US politics and Trump, would have liked to have more examples and deciphering on other international examples.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr class="border-b border-gray-100">
                        <td class="py-2 pr-4 align-top font-medium text-gray-900">The Heart of the Buddha's Teaching</td>
                        <td class="py-2 align-top text-gray-600">Covers core buddhist teachings. Could use more real life and down to earth examples to relate better to these key concepts. Never really managed to enter into a 'flow' state.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr class="border-b border-gray-100">
                        <td class="py-2 pr-4 align-top font-medium text-gray-900">The Sales Acceleration Formula</td>
                        <td class="py-2 align-top text-gray-600">Practical and data-driven approach to sales fed with Mark's experience at Hubspot. Plenty of actionable tips. Useful read.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr class="border-b border-gray-100">
                        <td class="py-2 pr-4 align-top font-medium text-gray-900">The Ride of a Lifetime: Lessons Learned from 15 Years as CEO of the Walt Disney Company</td>
                        <td class="py-2 align-top text-gray-600">One of the best business autobiography I've read. Interesting story, good storytelling, actionable examples. Definitely recommend if you're leading teams.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr class="border-b border-gray-100">
                        <td class="py-2 pr-4 align-top font-medium text-gray-900">Awareness: Conversations with the Masters</td>
                        <td class="py-2 align-top text-gray-600">Probably one of my favourite books on awareness and ancient wisdom in general. It's a recording of a conference given by Anthony De Mello. It's lively, fun and profound. I often come back to it to refresh my memory on the concepts.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr class="border-b border-gray-100">
                        <td class="py-2 pr-4 align-top font-medium text-gray-900">Daring Greatly</td>
                        <td class="py-2 align-top text-gray-600">Book that makes you see more clearly how your actions, words and behaviours impact others. As a parent, there are examples that I found particularly useful.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr class="border-b border-gray-100">
                        <td class="py-2 pr-4 align-top font-medium text-gray-900">Chaos: Making a New Science</td>
                        <td class="py-2 align-top text-gray-600">I had heard about the butterfly effect. Wanted to understand better what was behind it. Really an intro to the concept. Even when you calculate everything, there is a random layer that can have tremendous effect — in some fields more than others. e.g. weather prediction.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr class="border-b border-gray-100">
                        <td class="py-2 pr-4 align-top font-medium text-gray-900">The Fabric of Reality: The Science of Parallel Universes</td>
                        <td class="py-2 align-top text-gray-600">Super interesting field. Hard to listen to and remain engaged when you don't have the fundamentals of quantum physics.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr class="border-b border-gray-100">
                        <td class="py-2 pr-4 align-top font-medium text-gray-900">Outlive: The Science and Art of Longevity</td>
                        <td class="py-2 align-top text-gray-600">Didn't like the first part where Peter Attia explains his personal experience that led him to medicine 3.0. Found the rest exceptional. If you're into health and more precisely healthspan, definitely a must read. It's a trove of insights.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr class="border-b border-gray-100">
                        <td class="py-2 pr-4 align-top font-medium text-gray-900">Four Thousand Weeks</td>
                        <td class="py-2 align-top text-gray-600">Great book that puts things in perspective. Gives you real numbers about your life or the life of people you care about. Made me rethink how I allocate time with family and friends and where I put my priorities.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr class="border-b border-gray-100">
                        <td class="py-2 pr-4 align-top font-medium text-gray-900">The Relationship Handbook</td>
                        <td class="py-2 align-top text-gray-600">Short book that can help you better understand yourself and others, with a focus on relationships with others. Not a must read, several known concepts but good reminders. Probably good if you're starting with human psychology books.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr class="border-b border-gray-100">
                        <td class="py-2 pr-4 align-top font-medium text-gray-900">The Road Less Traveled</td>
                        <td class="py-2 align-top text-gray-600">Shares some interesting examples learned through his practice as a psychiatrist. Wasn't life changing for me though.</td>
                    </tr>
